        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(android): explain camera permission for setup scans",
        "body": "Closes #98044.\n\n### What Problem This Solves\nWhen Android setup QR scanning failed because Camera permission was denied, onboarding only showed generic scanner failure copy and did not guide users to grant the permission.\n\n### Evidence\nAt PR head `95764eea4c`, focused Play and third-party unit tests pass for `OnboardingFlowLogicTest`. They cover camera-specific scanner copy, the app-settings recovery decision, and that non-camera setup errors do not show the camera settings action.\n\nAndroid emulator proof on `sdk_gphone64_arm64`, Android 16 / API 36, using the Play debug APK (`versionName=2026.6.10`, `targetSdk=36`): with Camera revoked for OpenClaw and Google Play services, `Connect Gateway` -> `Scan setup code` first showed Google scanner `Camera permission required`; after dismissing it, Android requested `Allow OpenClaw Node to take pictures and record video?`; after `Don’t allow`, Gateway Setup showed `Camera permission is required to scan setup codes. Open Android app settings to grant Camera permission, then try again.` with the `Open app settings` action. A follow-up UI dump after leaving the camera-specific state no longer contained `Open app settings`.\n",
        "branch": "fix-98044-android-camera-permission",
